# Testing Conventions

## Framework
- JUnit 5 (`org.junit.jupiter.api.*`)
- AssertJ for assertions (`assertThat`, `assertThatThrownBy`, `assertThatCode`)
- Mockito for mocking (`@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)`)
- TestFX for JavaFX component testing

## Test Mode Isolation
- Build system sets `SpeleoDBConstants.TEST_MODE = true` before test compilation
- When TEST_MODE is true, preferences use an isolated node: `org/speleodb/ariane/plugin/speleodb/test`
- This prevents tests from corrupting real user preferences

## Test Structure
- Every test class MUST use JUnit 5 `@Test` annotations -- never `public static void main()`
- Use `@DisplayName` on all test classes and methods
- Use `@Nested` classes for logical grouping
- Test helpers go in `TestFixtures.java` and `TestEnvironmentConfig.java`

## JavaFX in Tests
- Headless rendering: system properties set in root `build.gradle` test block
- Initialize FX toolkit in `@BeforeAll`: `Platform.startup(() -> {})`
- Use `CountDownLatch` with timeout for async operations: `latch.await(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS)`
- Never busy-wait on the FX Application Thread

## Fixtures
- `TestFixtures` provides: project fixtures, TML file generation, SHA-256 checksums
- `TestFixtures.calculateChecksum()` delegates to `SpeleoDBService.calculateSHA256()`
- `TestEnvironmentConfig` loads `.env` for live API tests (optional)
- Test TML files go in `src/test/resources/artifacts/`

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- No `assert` keyword -- always use AssertJ
- No `catch (Exception ignored)` in tests -- assert the exception or let it propagate
- No duplicating production logic in testable inner classes -- use Mockito spies instead
- No test classes without `@Test` methods
